title: Philippines Manufacturing Production
description: Industrial Production in Philippines increased 10 percent in September of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Industrial Production in Philippines averaged 11.75 percent from 1986 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 531.30 percent in August of 2021 and a record low of -83.10 percent in August of 2020. In Philippines, Industrial Production is measured by the Value of Production Index (VaPI) of the manufacturing industry. This page provides - Philippines Industrial Production - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Philippine Statistics Authority
